author: Gareth Davies For Mailonline
title: Can you tell how many zebras are in this photograph? | Daily Mail Online
text: Stares and stripes: Can you tell how many zebras are in this photograph? You'll need to look very closely... Retired mechanical engineer Robert Holmwood captured the gaggle of Burchell's zebra in South Africa They were at the Kruger National Park in his native country and the image has caused mass confusion The 64-year-old said his friends have been guessing a variety of numbers People who have seen the optical illusion think there are anything between four and seven zebras in the snap Published: 10:31 GMT, 9 February 2017 | Updated: 17:17 GMT, 9 February 2017 131 shares
